[SN]TITLE[SN]
Worker hurt in 60ft digger fall in Coventry

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A worker was hurt when a digger plunged 20m (60ft) into a rubbish pit at a recycling plant.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident happened at the Waste to Energy plant in Bar Road, Coventry, the city council said.
It took three hours to rescue the man, who was treated for "relatively minor injuries".
The authority said it was "co-operating fully" with emergency services and the Health and Safety Executive.
West Midlands Ambulance Service said crews were called at 10:30 BST.
